description:
What does the Sabbath mean to you?

The Sabbath is the memorial of Gods rest after He finished the Creation of the world, and it is a celebration of the perfect world He is preparing for us in heaven.

This #short clip from the Global #Campmeeting sermon, The Epistle of Apostle Paul: The Message of Hebrews and Its Relevance Today https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nWjUgpCIWRE&list=PL-k2Gb-DBYo9tb9fHW_AxGxJ1R8MpNnpa&index=36  serves as a reminder that by observing the Sabbath, we are not only acknowledging God as our Creator but also as our Redeemer. 

Watch the video to learn more about the epistle of the Apostle Paul, which will strengthen our faith in these final days and remind us of the importance of the Sabbath.
